Relay teams from affluent countries are the most frequent winners in the Olympics.
The four relay finals will dominate this evening's games in Barcelona.
Over the years, the US has won the most relay medals followed by Britain and the former Soviet Union.
The Cuban women's 100 meters relay teams in 1968 and 1972 are the only women outside the developed world to win gold.
Carl Lewis will pursue his eighth Olympic gold as a member of a very strong US team.
In a completed event, Voula Patoulidou of Greece won the gold in womens 100m. 
